---
source: crates/loom/tests/cli_help.rs
expression: "loom_help(&[\"gate\", \"audit\"])"
---
Run every deterministic verifier followed by the LLM rubric (`verify` then `review`). The full PR-gate path

Usage: loom gate audit [OPTIONS] [SELECTOR]

Arguments:
  [SELECTOR]  Run one specific verifier by its annotation target (e.g. a command string for `[check]` / `[system]`, a test path for `[test]`, a rubric path for `[judge]`)

Options:
      --files <PATH>      Scope to verifiers whose declared inputs intersect this file set
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -s, --spec <LABEL>      Filter to one spec's criteria. Defaults to `current_spec` when applicable to the subcommand
  -b, --bead <ID>         Scope to one bead's success-criteria inputs and the bead's own diff
      --diff <RANGE>      Scope to a git diff range. Default when no scope flag is set: `<molecule.base_commit>..HEAD` for the active molecule, else `HEAD`
      --tree              Scope to every file in the workspace (nightly safety net)
  -h, --help              Print help
